.TH hsh 1 "April 2026" "Holberton simple_shell" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hsh \- simple UNIX command interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a simple command-line interpreter.
It reads commands from standard input, interprets them, and runs programs.

Implemented behavior:
.RS
- command and arguments (split on spaces/tabs)
.br
- PATH search
.br
- built-ins: exit, env
.br
- no pipes/redirections/advanced parsing
.RE

Interactive mode prints `($) ` before reading a command.
Non-interactive mode reads from piped or redirected input.

Error messages are aligned with
.B /bin/sh
format for command-not-found cases, except that the program name is
.B argv[0]
of
.BR hsh .
.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns shell exit status.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.B PATH
is used to locate executables when a command has no slash.
.SH EXAMPLES
Interactive mode:
.PP
.B ./hsh
.br
($) /bin/ls
.br
($) exit

Non-interactive mode:
.PP
.B echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sh (1),
.BR execve (2),
.BR fork (2),
.BR waitpid (2)
.SH AUTHORS
See
.B AUTHORS
file.
